-- OTP Bank Rises Second Day, Heads for First Weekly Gain in May
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-25T10:26:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/otp-bank-rises-second-day-heads-for-first-weekly-gain-in-may.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) , Hungary’s largest
lender, gained for a second day, heading for its first weekly
advance this month.  The shares increased 3.2 percent to 3,522 forint by 12:07
p.m. in Budapest. A close at that level would mean a 2.8 percent
five-day increase. The benchmark BUX stock  index  rose 1.7
percent for a weekly gain of 0.7 percent.  European stocks rallied after  Italy ’s Prime Minister  Mario
Monti  said that most European Union leaders support joint bonds
for the euro area.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
